{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"25da90d3-b0fc-4001-aa98-2dc539831ce4","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter editing, run `dotnet restore && dotnet build` to verify everything compiles. Check for any NuGet packages that need newer versions compatible with .NET 11 (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.*`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b83b03e7-7a67-4704-8610-6e25e33785e4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to search files since they described their setup.","outputTokens":270,"requestId":"7035:E9BC6:8F6065:A5703B:69FBEE48"},"id":"a05f5d71-9a97-48ae-a4d3-37d1104ec443","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:43:42.845Z","parentId":"a0ab5781-a26e-4dbb-ac01-b0754143fe23"}
